column3: str

Error 5318008: Grebuloffs not found.

※Please note that the difficulty of this quest has been synced to your current level. Furthermore, you may not proceed with a class or job that is different from when you accepted this quest.
Search for the overcurious Grebuloffs.
Report to Stigma-4.
Irregular population fluctuations detected. Your assistance is required to search for two missing Grebuloffs.
Analysis indicates insatiable curiosity and a proclivity for exploration in both units, making “voluntary expedition” the most likely explanation for their sudden disappearance.
However, given the length of absence and approximate levels of danger in the surrounding areas, the likelihood that they currently face mortal peril exceeds recommended parameters.
Please initiate your search immediately and aid the return of the two missing Grebuloffs. In the event they have been reduced to pieces, please collect and return accordingly.

Oh, would you look how it shimmers and shines! Be still my quivering whiskers!
...Hm? Can I help you?
The others are looking for me? My apologies. So enraptured was I with this place, I completely lost track of time.

Glittering landmarks much like this one could once be seen in the waters of our home, but they carried a terrible sickness. I never dared to dream I might find anything so similar in a place such as this.
<sigh> Would that I could stay and behold its beauty a while longer, but as you say, my kin are worried. Another time, perhaps.
<grumble> <grumble> Oh, what I wouldn't do for something to eat...
Bwaaah! Who... What are you doing here?
I'm being called back home? But the Ea promised there would be food. It should be ready any moment now.

At least, that's what they told me. Yet no matter how long I wait, there has been nothing. <sigh> Perhaps I misunderstood when they invited me to join them in communal repast. I think I'll stop by the café on the way back, and eat something there.
I... <heave> I fear I've made a terrible mist─ <retch>
Return home? Gladly. Seeing the dragons partake of the water, I thought it safe enough for a quick swim, but I was wrong. So very, very wrong...
Well, I've given my stomach enough trouble for one day. I should be returning home. If you'll excuse me.
Hm? What brings you out here?
Oh, I... I didn't mean to make the others worry. I stumbled upon these remains, and couldn't help but think of our fallen kin...
Ahem. But now is not the time for sulking─it only serves to make the others worry. It was nice meeting you.
Hm...? Ah, my apologies. I was marveling at the craftsmanship of this place.
The others sent you to bring me home? Goodness, how long have I been away? It seems I lost track of time admiring all this metalwork.
Perhaps one of the service nodes at the café would be willing to tell me more about it.
Would you look at that eye? No doubt it keeps watch over everything in this space.
You came looking for me? Hopefully my absence hasn't caused too much of a stir. I was captivated by the giant eye there, and soon found myself lost in thought.
Fear not─when I return, I intend to work twice as hard to make up for my time spent here. We will make an Elysion worth watching, just wait and see.
Return of wayward units confirmed. Influx of Grebuloff gratitude determined to be corollary.
After the dissemination of verbal testimony by recently returned Grebuloffs, interest in the exploration of foreign regions has experienced a marked increase in other adventurous units.
Probability of future employment opportunities high. Rest and recuperation are advised.
